{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2f94caff",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For measurement error mitigation, we will use the matrix-free measurement mitigation (mthree) package.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Python Package:**  \n",
    "https://qiskit.org/ecosystem/mthree/index.html  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Paper:**  \n",
    "Scalable Mitigation of Measurement Errors on Quantum Computers  \n",
    "*Paul D. Nation, Hwajung Kang, Neereja Sundaresan, and Jay M. Gambetta*  \n",
    "PRX Quantum 2, 040326 â€“ Published 8 November 2021  \n",
    "https://journals.aps.org/prxquantum/abstract/10.1103/PRXQuantum.2.040326"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5f490f15",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "bb5a90fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from qiskit import *\n",
    "from qiskit.providers.fake_provider import FakeMumbai\n",
    "from qiskit.result import sampled_expectation_value\n",
    "from qiskit_aer import AerSimulator\n",
    "\n",
    "import mthree\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib_inline\n",
    "matplotlib_inline.backend_inline.set_matplotlib_formats('retina')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "67b75a4e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "662df92a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_hadamard_chain(num_qubits):\n",
    "    qc = QuantumCircuit(num_qubits)\n",
    "    qc.x(range(0, num_qubits))\n",
    "    qc.h(range(0, num_qubits))\n",
    "    for kk in range(num_qubits//2,0,-1):\n",
    "        qc.ch(kk, kk-1)\n",
    "    for kk in range(num_qubits//2, N-1):\n",
    "        qc.ch(kk, kk+1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    return qc"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d9646e12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 807.192x1036.78 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {
      "image/png": {
       "height": 818,
       "width": 641
      }
     },
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "N = 12\n",
    "qc = create_hadamard_chain(num_qubits=N)\n",
    "qc.draw('mpl', fold=-1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "028f047d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "qc_plus_meas = qc.measure_all(inplace=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "cfb9c3b9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "backend = FakeMumbai()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "5ec77739",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ideal_simulator = AerSimulator()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "8646cd2d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trans_qc = transpile(qc_plus_meas, backend, optimization_level=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4b92f8dc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Getting final maps of physical qubits using mthree"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1948b68",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To mitigate measurement error, we need to know finally from which *physical qubits* the data was read out because depending on the physical qubits the measurement error rates can vary. With M3, finding out the final physical qubits (final measurement maps) are as easy as a function call. Note that, we need to supply the transpiled quantum circuits as they have the accurate final measurement mappings (Transpiler can map the virtual qubits of your circuit to any set of physical qubits depening on the choice of initial layout (map) method. Besides, the routing stage of the transpiler can change layout to meet the device connectivity. Thus, your final measurement mappings can be non-trivial)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "b8c9be78",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "measured_qubits = mthree.utils.final_measurement_mapping(trans_qc)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "260a8366",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{0: 19,\n",
       " 1: 22,\n",
       " 2: 25,\n",
       " 3: 24,\n",
       " 4: 23,\n",
       " 5: 21,\n",
       " 6: 18,\n",
       " 7: 15,\n",
       " 8: 12,\n",
       " 9: 10,\n",
       " 10: 7,\n",
       " 11: 4}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "measured_qubits"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "de6b33ff",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Run measurement calibration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "062acc24",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After knowing the final measurement mappings, we need to run calibration circuits to quanitfy the readout error probabilities."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "27e196fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calibration\n",
    "mit = mthree.M3Mitigation(backend)\n",
    "mit.cals_from_system(measured_qubits)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7d01412f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Executing main circuit"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "bac49b9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_counts = backend.run(trans_qc, shots=10000).result().get_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "07e5552a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_expval = sampled_expectation_value(dist=raw_counts, oper=\"Z\"*N)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7fe7f41b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Applying measurement mitigation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "2a38b37e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Applying measurement correction using M3, converts the Counts into quasi probability distributions\n",
    "quasi_probs = mit.apply_correction(raw_counts, measured_qubits)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "df79c0fe",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mitigated_expval = sampled_expectation_value(dist=quasi_probs, oper=\"Z\"*N)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "e718b127",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ideal_counts = ideal_simulator.run(trans_qc, shots=10000).result().get_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "8653b0fa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ideal_expval = sampled_expectation_value(dist=ideal_counts, oper=\"Z\"*N)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "e3224ba3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Ideal expectation value: 0.4340\n",
      "Raw expectation value: 0.1616\n",
      "Mitigated expectation value: 0.4070\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"Ideal expectation value: {ideal_expval:0.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Raw expectation value: {raw_expval:0.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mitigated expectation value: {mitigated_expval:0.4f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "f6608a06",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "print(f\"mthree version {mthree.__version__}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy\n",
    "print(f\"numpy version {numpy.__version__}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import qiskit_ibm_runtime\n",
